cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on analyzing the performance of Multipath TCP over two LTE connections. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the security implications of using MPTCP over multiple LTE connections. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper discusses the impact of application traffic patterns on MPTCP adaptability. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper discusses the impact of MPTCP performance on multimedia applications. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is a possible category as the paper analyzes the performance of MPTCP over dual LTE connections in different scenarios.
